Female (paratype in 
UBC-SEM
). Carapace length 1.89; abdomen length 2.45. Carapace (Fig. 33): As in male. First leg tibia with five pairs of ventral spines. Epigyne (Figs 23, 24): With triangular openings pointing to the posterior. Colour in alcohol (Fig. 33): As in male, but with weaker dark patches on first legs.

The range of this species may extend to the east. A female (specimen PNG2008-3321 in 
UBC-SEM
) slightly differing in epigynal structure is tentatively assigned to this species. It is pictured in Figs 34-37, and has data: PAPUA NEW GUINEA: Eastern Highlands Province: Mt Gahavisuka Provincial Park. S 6.015 E 145.412. elev. 2320 m a.s.l. 1-2 August 2008. W Maddison leg. WPM#08-025.
